, , ',1,1,1,1,1,'uk-UA','2023-07-14 10:14:58',100,'2023-07-14 10:14:58',100),(10,5,'Fire-resistant bioplastic made from single-celled algae','fire-resistant-bioplastic-made-from-single-celled-algae','img_9049.jpg','Researchers have developed a new bioplastic from the blue-green cells of cyanobacteria commonly known as spirulina.','<div>Rich in vitamins and minerals, spirulina is a type of blue-green algae. They are commonly used as a health supplement. Now researchers have used spirulina to create a new type of bioplastic that decomposes in a compost pit in the same amount of time it takes a banana peel.</div><div>Bioplastic is entirely made from powdered biomass of cyanobacteria. Using heat and pressure  the same process used to create conventional plastics  the researchers shaped the spirulina powder into various shapes.</div><div><br></div><div>Spirulina was chosen because it can be cultivated on a large scale, and the cyanobacteria cells fix carbon dioxide as they grow. This makes spirulina carbon neutral and potentially carbon negative. In addition, it is fire resistant.</div><div><br></div><div>When exposed to fire, the bioplastic made from spirulina self-extinguishes instantly, unlike many traditional plastics that either burn or melt, explains Harish Ayer, lead author of the study.</div><div><br></div><div>The study was published in the journal&nbsp;<a href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/adfm.202302067\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); box-sizing: inherit; text-decoration-skip-ink: auto; transition: color 0.2s ease-in-out;\">Advanced Functional Materials.</a></div>','Fire-resistant bioplastic made from single-celled algae','Researchers have developed a new bioplastic from the blue-green cells of cyanobacteria commonly known as spirulina.','spirulina, algae, flame retardant, bioplastic',1,1,1,1,1,'en-US','2023-07-14 10:17:23',100,'2023-07-14 10:17:23',100),(11,4,'In the US, robots began to patrol the territory of some schools to improve safety','in-the-us-robots-began-to-patrol-the-territory-of-some-schools-to-improve-safety','im-812660_large.jpg','The United States has launched a pilot program in which robots provide additional security in some schools.','<p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">The project in New Mexico County was launched in mid-June. A four-wheeled robot more than one and a half meters high and weighing about 180 kg patrols the school campus around the clock and seven days a week. The robot is equipped with cameras that provide a 360-degree view, the images of which are sent to the security service.</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">In addition, at least the robot in Santa Fe is equipped with an artificial intelligence system. It looks at the school\'s normal business patterns and detects people who are on campus after hours or who are engaging in violent behavior. That is, AI can help prevent a crime, and not just fix it.</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">Also, the robot can determine if people have weapons, but this function was turned off for the duration of the pilot project.</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\"><img src=\"https://demo.butterflycms.com/uploads/media/2023/07/im-812651_large.jpg\"><br></p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">The robot itself does not have any weapons, but it is equipped with a speaker through which security officers can talk to suspicious people or criminals if the crime has already taken place.</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">But the robot is not endowed with the function of face recognition. Apparently, in order to avoid claims from the parents of the students.</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">The issue of school safety in the US is becoming more acute amid recent shootings, and robots may well help make schools safer.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 1.45em;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 1.45em;\">Source:&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.ixbt.com/click/?&amp;h=ccefe5a43966e74686a246b7e206069567b62330\" title=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/this-schools-new-security-aide-has-360-degree-vision-its-a-robot-a4f983b5?mod=djemalertNEWS\">The Wall Street Journal</a></p>','In the US, robots began to patrol the territory of some schools to improve safety','The United States has launched a pilot program in which robots provide additional security in some schools.','USA, robots, AI',1,1,1,1,1,'en-US','2023-07-14 11:04:15',100,'2023-07-14 11:04:15',100),(12,4,'          ','u-ssa-roboti-pocali-patruluvati-teritorii-deakih-skil-dla-pidvisenna-bezpeki','im-812660_large.jpg','    ,          .','<p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">   -     .          180         .   ,   360- ,      .</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\"> ,    -    .         ,           .      ,     .</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">      ,         .</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\"><img src=\"https://demo.butterflycms.com/uploads/media/2023/07/im-812651_large.jpg\"><br></p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">     ,    ,             ,     .</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">       . ,       .</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.45em;\">             ,        .</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 1.45em;\">:&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.ixbt.com/click/?&amp;h=ccefe5a43966e74686a246b7e206069567b62330\" title=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/this-schools-new-security-aide-has-360-degree-vision-its-a-robot-a4f983b5?mod=djemalertNEWS\">The Wall Street Journal</a></p>','          ','    ,          .',', , ',1,1,1,1,1,'uk-UA','2023-07-14 11:04:34',100,'2023-07-14 11:04:34',100),(13,3,'Starlink satellites evaded collisions with other objects 25 thousand times in six months','starlink-satellites-evaded-collisions-with-other-objects-25-thousand-times-in-six-months','starlinkiau.jpg','Starlink communications satellites have to dodge collisions with other man-made objects in space thousands of times every month.','<p>Starlink communications satellites have to dodge collisions with other man-made objects in space thousands of times every month. According to data filed by SpaceX with the US Federal Communications Commission, from December 1, 2022 to May 21, 2023, the satellites had to perform 25,000 evasive maneuvers.<br>According to the company, the threshold for the start of maneuvering of its satellites is an order of magnitude more stringent than the industry standard - satellites begin to change orbit when the probability of collision exceeds 1:100,000, while NASA and other companies set the threshold at 1:10. 000.</p><p>Numerous maneuvers in an orbit full of spacecraft only fuel the fears of many experts, warning that catastrophic collisions in the future are inevitable. At the same time, it is reported that in the previous six months, when there were significantly fewer Starlink satellites in orbit, there were half as many maneuvers - during the reporting period, the group grew by 457 vehicles.</p><p>SpaceX is not the only company with plans to create a mega constellation in orbit. Even if some projects fail to materialize, there will still be tens of thousands of new satellites from various companies in space by the end of the decade.</p><p>Just a few days after the report, a study was published in the journal Astronomy &amp; Astrophysics, indicating that some Starlink satellites also \"glow\" in the radio range, interfering with radio telescopes, not counting the fact that they interfere with observations in the optical range. The \"visibility\" of satellites in the radio range is of great concern to astronomers, since there are virtually no national and international laws to protect their observations.</p><p>Lead author of the study is Federico Di Vruno, one of the directors of the International Astronomical Union\'s (IAU) Center for the Protection of Dark and Silent Sky, which is constantly sounding the alarm about the negative impact of satellite constellations on astronomical observations. It is known that the authors of the report are in close contact with SpaceX, and it has already introduced changes to the next generation of Starlink satellites that will reduce the negative impact on the work of scientists.</p><p>Source:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"techcrunch.com\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(16, 92, 150); text-decoration: underline; outline: 0px;\">techcrunch.com</a></p>','Starlink satellites evaded collisions with other objects 25 thousand times in six months','Starlink communications satellites have to dodge collisions with other man-made objects in space thousands of times every month.','Starlink, SpaceX, satellites',1,1,1,1,1,'en-US','2023-07-14 11:10:53',100,'2023-07-14 11:10:53',100),(14,3,' Starlink      \' 25 .   ','suputniki-starlink-uhililisa-vid-zitknen-z-insimi-obektami-25-tis-raziv-za-pivroku','starlinkiau.jpg',' \' Starlink       \'      .','<p> \' Starlink       \'      .   ,  SpaceX     \' ,  1  2022   21  2023     25 .  .<br>   ,         ,  ,    ,     ,     1:100 000,    NASA        1:10. 000.</p><p>   ,   ,     ,    ,      .   ,   ,   Starlink     ,      -       457 .</p><p>SpaceX -         .         ,               .</p><p>        Astronomy &amp; Astrophysics   ,    ,    Starlink     ,  ,   ,       .       ,           .</p><p>       (Federico Di Vruno),              (IAU),   \'   \'        . ,         SpaceX          Starlink,        .</p><p>:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"techcrunch.com\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(16, 92, 150); text-decoration: underline; outline: 0px;\">techcrunch.com</a></p>',' Starlink      \' 25 .   ',' \' Starlink       \'      .','Starlink, SpaceX, ',1,1,1,1,1,'uk-UA','2023-07-14 11:11:04',100,'2023-07-14 11:11:04',100),(15,2,'BMW priced smart projection glasses for motorcyclists at 690 euros','bmw-priced-smart-projection-glasses-for-motorcyclists-at-690-euros','bmw_01.jpg','BMW has offered motorcycle owners glasses with a tiny projector that allows you to see the necessary information in front of your eyes.','<p>While automakers have long used augmented reality elements, projecting instrument readings and navigation tips onto a specific area of the windshield in front of the drivers eyes, it is more difficult for motorcycle manufacturers to achieve similar goals. BMW solved this problem by offering motorcycle owners glasses with a tiny projector that allows you to see the necessary information in front of your eyes.</p><p>The ConnectedRide device, according to Gizmodo, resembles sports glasses with light filters, while the lenses are interchangeable. The user can both change the degree of their transparency by replacing one set with another, and the curvature of the surface - you can change the diopter values in accordance with the prescriptions of doctors. On the surface of the right lens in front of the driver\'s eye, information about the speed of movement, the current gear of the motorcycle, the speed limit on this section of the road, as well as hints from the navigation system is projected.</p><p>The customer can choose between two dimensions of BMW ConnectedRide goggles, depending on the distance between the pupils of the eyes. The case, which is quite elegant for a device with built-in electronics, houses a battery that allows the glasses to be used for 10 hours without recharging. New BMW motorcycle models must support wireless pairing with these goggles. At least the electric BMW CE 02 is compatible with this very useful accessory.</p><p>Source:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://gizmodo.com/bmw-motorcycle-connectedride-smartglasses-1850621202\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: justify;\">Gizmodo</a></p>','BMW priced smart projection glasses for motorcyclists at 690 euros','BMW has offered motorcycle owners glasses with a tiny projector that allows you to see the necessary information in front of your eyes.','BMW, smart projection glasses, glasses, VAR',1,1,1,1,1,'en-US','2023-07-14 11:16:56',100,'2023-07-14 11:16:56',100),(16,2,'BMW        690 ','bmw-ocinila-rozumni-proekcijni-okulari-dla-motociklistiv-u-690-evro','bmw_01.jpg','BMW       ,        .','<p>       ,              ,        . BMW   ,       ,       .</p><p> ConnectedRide,   Gizmodo,       ,     .            ,     -        .            ,   ,      ,     .</p><p>        BMW ConnectedRide,      .           ,      10   .    BMW       . ,  BMW CE 02      .</p><p>:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://gizmodo.com/bmw-motorcycle-connectedride-smartglasses-1850621202\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: justify;\">Gizmodo</a></p>','BMW        690 ','BMW       ,        .','BMW,   , , VAR',1,1,1,1,1,'uk-UA','2023-07-14 11:17:04',100,'2023-07-14 11:17:04',100),(17,1,'IBM will entrust Samsung with the release of its own processors for artificial intelligence systems','ibm-will-entrust-samsung-with-the-release-of-its-own-processors-for-artificial-intelligence-systems','bmw_01.jpg','The contract division of the Korean company will also produce specialized processors for artificial intelligence systems for IBM.','<p>Once upon a time, IBM acted as a technology donor for GlobalFoundries and even sold its processor manufacturing enterprises to the latter, but the buyer eventually decided not to pursue advanced lithography, which forced the blue giant to turn to Samsung Electronics. The contract division of the Korean company will also produce specialized processors for artificial intelligence systems for IBM.</p><p>According to IBM representatives cited by Reuters, the company has developed processors for its own needs, designed to accelerate the work of artificial intelligence cloud systems \"watsonx\". These processors have a rather narrow scope, allowing the corresponding systems to quickly draw logical conclusions based on the results of processing large amounts of data and training models.</p><p>More than a decade ago, IBM tried to shape the market for artificial intelligence systems with its Watson platform, but then the high cost of components and high operating costs became an obstacle to its widespread adoption. The appearance in the arsenal of IBM specialized processors of its own design allows partly to solve this problem. At the very least, with higher power efficiency, these processors can reduce power consumption.</p><p>The existence of Artificial Intelligence Unit processors became known back in October last year, but then IBM did not disclose who would produce them and where they would be used. The release of processors was entrusted to Samsung Electronics, and now IBM already has several thousand working prototypes. When the processors of this family will become available to third-party customers, it is not specified.</p><p>As Mukesh Khare, director of IBM Semiconductors, noted in an interview, the company does not seek to create substitutes for NVIDIA\'s widely used accelerators in the industry. If the latter are tailored for training language models, then IBM solutions are designed to accelerate the formation of logical conclusions based on the collected data and decision making in artificial intelligence systems. An IBM representative emphasized that the company is convinced of its ability to significantly influence this particular market segment.</p><p>Source:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/ibm-mulls-using-its-own-ai-chip-new-cloud-service-lower-costs-2023-07-11/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(16, 92, 150); text-decoration: underline; outline: 0px;\">Reuters</a></p>','IBM will entrust Samsung with the release of its own processors for artificial intelligence systems','The contract division of the Korean company will also produce specialized processors for artificial intelligence systems for IBM.','IBM, Samsung, processors',1,1,1,1,1,'en-US','2023-07-14 11:24:18',100,'2023-07-14 11:24:18',100),(18,1,'IBM  Samsung       ','ibm-dovirit-samsung-vipusk-vlasnih-procesoriv-dla-sistem-stucnogo-intelektu','bmw_01.jpg','     IBM       .','<p>  IBM       GlobalFoundries         ,          ,   \" \"    Samsung Electronics.      IBM       .</p><p>   IBM,    Reuters,     ,        watsonx.       ,                .</p><p>    IBM           Watson,               .    IBM         . ,    ,      .</p><p>   Artificial Intelligence Unit       ,   IBM  ,   ,     .     Samsung Electronics,   IBM         .        ,  .</p><p>   \'  IBM Semiconductors   (Mukesh Khare),         NVIDIA,     .       ,  IBM                .  IBM ,             .</p><p>:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/ibm-mulls-using-its-own-ai-chip-new-cloud-service-lower-costs-2023-07-11/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(16, 92, 150); text-decoration: underline; outline: 0px;\">Reuters</a></p>','IBM  Samsung       ','     IBM       .','IBM, Samsung, ',1,1,1,1,1,'uk-UA','2023-07-14 11:24:39',100,'2023-07-14 11:24:39',100);
